### Phase Summary

**📌 Phase 1 — Foundation & Quick Wins** (5 features, all MUST)
1. **Privacy Badge & Zero-Tracking Guarantee** — Make the #1 differentiator visible & auditable *(addresses Todoist, Google, TickTick privacy pain points)*
2. **Task Count & Progress Summary Bar** — Real-time active/completed counter
3. **Bulk Clear Completed** — One-click remove all done tasks *(addresses Any.do's permanent deletion pain point)*
4. **Global Keyboard Shortcut to Focus Input** — Press `/` from anywhere to start typing
5. **Progressive Web App (PWA)** — Installable, fully offline capable *(addresses sync failures in MS To Do, TickTick)*

**🚀 Phase 2 — Enhancement & Differentiation** (6 features, all SHOULD)
6. Dark Mode with system preference detection
7. Optional Due Dates *(addresses Google Tasks' half-baked date support)*
8. Priority Levels (High / Medium / Low) *(addresses Google Tasks & TickTick gaps)*
9. One-Click Task Export (JSON & plain text) *(addresses vendor lock-in across all 5 competitors)*
10. Drag-and-Drop Reordering *(addresses TickTick's ordering bugs)*
11. LocalStorage Quota Error Handling (technical debt)

**⚡ Phase 3 — Scale & Power User Features** (4 features, all COULD)
12. Task Categories & Tags
13. Subtasks & Task Notes
14. Recurring Tasks *(free version of TickTick/Any.do paywalled feature)*
15. In-App Keyboard Shortcut Help Sheet

**🔭 Phase 4 — Future Vision** (4 features, all WON'T for now)
16. Optional E2E Encrypted Cloud Sync
17. PWA Push Notifications & Local Reminders
18. Code Architecture Refactoring & Build System
19. Automated Test Suite

